    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL CHALLENGES W.T.O. RULING</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil will appeal World Trade Organization ruling against export subsidies for aircraft maker Embraer; faces trade sanctions by Canada, home of rival Bombardier (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Brazilian government will appeal a World Trade Organization ruling against export subsidies for the aircraft maker Embraer, a leading maker of small passenger jets. If the ruling is upheld, Canada, home to Embraer's rival Bombardier, could retaliate with up to $3.3 billion in trade sanctions in the next seven years. Canadian and Brazilian trade negotiators will meet on May 23 in hopes of resolving the dispute. Canada was also cited by the W.T.O. for its subsidies to Bombardier, but the Canadian government has said it will respect the ruling.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
